  <bodyText><![CDATA[<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">If you're looking for a holiday that will take you off the beaten track and give you a true sense of adventure, then look no further than our range of mountain walking holidays across Europe. Here, you'll experience authentic and unforgettable experiences that explore the landscapes of Europe's most spectacular mountain ranges.</span></p>
<p><img style="width: 100%; height: auto;" src="/media/13085278/kranjska_gora-2.jpg?width=0&amp;height=0" alt="" data-udi="umb://media/129cc1c1b0bb4d24b1373804c4ac1f8a" /></p>
<h2>What to expect from our walking holidays in the mountains</h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">When you travel with us, you'll be able to choose from a wide range of different hiking routes that suit all fitness levels and experience. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">From leading you through some of the most stunning scenery around, to helping you discover hidden gems that only locals know about, our expert guides will ensure that each day of your trip is full of fresh experiences. It's more than just a walk in the park!</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Whether you want to explore mountain trails, ascend into mountain villages, hike through flower-filled meadows or scale one of Europe's highest peaks - we promise that this will be an experience you'll never forget!</span></p>
<p> </p>
<div class="g4">
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<h3>Free guided walks included in your holiday</h3>
<p><img style="width: 100%px; height: autopx;" src="/media/13093530/close-up-feet.png?width=0&amp;height=0" alt="" data-udi="umb://media/ada05f0bc8de4c3d84cb81a1965dba1d" /></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">We love showing our guests the best places to visit, so join one of our expert-led guided walks and get the most out of your trip. </span></p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="g4">
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<h3>Our self-guided walking holidays offer total flexibility</h3>
<p><img style="width: 100%px; height: auto;" src="/media/13093531/close-up-walking.png?width=0&amp;height=0" alt="" data-udi="umb://media/6a1275fcf4c849cc870dc70996b0952e" /></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Enjoy the freedom and flexibility of a self-guided walking holiday. Explore at your own pace, with each day's route entirely up to you.</span></p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="g4">
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<h3>See more, do more and discover more</h3>
<p><img style="width: autopx; height: 100%;" src="/media/13080490/merano-tourist-board-image-8.jpg?width=500&amp;height=268.49642004773267" alt="" data-udi="umb://media/ddef516ea88a4726b9a4ac183045b915" /></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Travel with us and experience walking holidays in a whole new light, we promise you that there'll be so much more to see and do than on a typical walking holiday.</span></p>
</div>
</div>
<p> </p>
<h2>Choosing a destination</h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Scale the stunning Dolomites, tackle one of Slovenia’s beautiful mountains or climb Mont Blanc. Whether you're looking for a challenge or just want to relax with some great views, we have a walking holiday that’s right for you.</span></p>
<h3>Discover the best mountain holidays in Europe</h3>
<div class="g6">
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<h2>Austria</h2>
<p><img style="width: 100%; height: auto;" src="/media/13085192/mayhofen-views.jpg?width=0&amp;height=0" alt="" data-udi="umb://media/f088f422b70248f4a451e298cdb4db28" /></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Built for walking, Mayrhofen is a mountain world of discovery. Whether you are looking for relaxed walks through the most beautiful hiking trails or want to challenge yourself in climbing the Ahorn and Penken, this region offers something for every type of walker.</span></p>
<p><strong>Mountain walking highlights:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>Penken &amp; Ahorn</strong>: Enjoy a beautiful day in the mountains with some stunning views. The two cable cars open up extensive trails above the village, including the Ahorn mountain, which has a lovely loop walk and daily birds of prey show.</span></li>
<li><span style="font-weight: 400;"></span><span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>Stillup Valley</strong>: Stillup Valley will delight nature lovers and adventurers with three waterfalls falling into a turquoise reservoir, backed by snow capped Italian mountains. This iconic hiking destination is accessible on the bus service with some challenging but rewarding hikes to huts in the valley basin.</span></li>
<li><span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>Berliner Hutte:</strong> A walk to remember. Visit the Berliner Hutte at 2042 metres, an imposing cultural icon and a rich natural beauty. This all day event is perfect for keen walkers and sightseers alike.</span></li>
</ul>
<p><strong><a data-udi="umb://document/594483304a5f4b47844b444df2c9d975" href="/{localLink:umb://document/594483304a5f4b47844b444df2c9d975}" title="Mayrhofen">Find out more about Mayrhofen &gt;&gt;</a></strong></p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="g6">
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<h2>Switzerland</h2>
<p><img style="width: 100%; height: auto;" src="/media/13077666/maennlichen-eigernordwand-grindelwald.jpg?width=0&amp;height=0" alt="" data-udi="umb://media/1e3ee09ff2ff4fdbbbae99d4e7ed58de" /></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Grindelwald is surrounded by the high peaks of the Bernese Alps, with over 500 kilometres of well laid out paths to choose between and many panoramic views of the Eiger, Mönch and Jungfrau mountains. The village itself is a good base from which to explore some of Switzerland’s most dramatic mountain scenery.</span></p>
<p><strong>Mountain walking highlights:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Mountain Panorama Trail</strong>:<span style="font-weight: 400;"> This is a great walk for the whole family. You can start this walk from top of First mountain and walk over to Grosse Scheidegg and then catch the yellow Grindelwald Bus back into the resort or do the other way round.</span></li>
<li><strong>Männlichen to the Kleine Scheidegg</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;">: Take the classic of all panorama hikes. The spectacular views of the Eiger, Mönch and Jungfrau mountains on this leisurely and unique panorama trail are captivating.</span></li>
<li><span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>Eiger Trail:</strong> The Eiger Trail is the closest one can get to the famous Eiger North Face. Those with the will and courage to get just that little bit closer to its breath-taking peaks and tackle a superlative high alpine adventure can take the Jungfrau Railway to the station at Eigergletscher and set out on a unique tour.</span></li>
</ul>
<p><strong><a data-udi="umb://document/0fe9200934b24cd49d20e1cea080f5da" href="/{localLink:umb://document/0fe9200934b24cd49d20e1cea080f5da}" title="Grindelwald">Find out more about Grindelwald &gt;&gt;</a></strong></p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="g6">
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<h2>Italy</h2>
<p><img style="width: 100%; height: auto;" src="/media/2000/selva_big.jpg?width=0&amp;height=0" alt="" data-udi="umb://media/606a201d8c1f45a6890b7f826deeeff1" /></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Selva offers a range of hiking trails and lifts so you don't have to go far to see some stunning scenery. Bring your camera so you can capture some incredible pictures of  wild flowers in bloom. Walk miles of trails or take the lift up higher! Great for challenging, moderate and easy hikes.</span></p>
<p><strong>Mountain walking highlights:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Panascharte to the Seceda</strong>: <span style="font-weight: 400;">If you’re a fan of sweeping panoramic views and stunning mountain scenes, the hike to Seceda is for you. Starting at the cable car in Ortisei, this walk takes you up to one of Europe's most scenic peaks. It can get busy so try to go early in summer and bring plenty of water.</span></p>
</li>
<li>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;"></span><span style="font-weight: 400;"></span><strong>Pic Mountain</strong>: <span style="font-weight: 400;">With breath taking views, the Pic Mountain walk is one you won't forget. The cable car from San Cristina takes you part of the way up, but it's a strenuous walk in the other direction to reach the summit and lookout point Sëurasas. This hike is great for those who want to test their legs and escape crowds.</span></p>
</li>
<li><span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>The Sassolongo</strong>: This walk takes you through some of the most stunning scenery in the Dolomites. Starting at Ciampinoi lift, follow the Friedrich August path and take in the stunning views over Seiser Alm, the biggest high alpine pasture in Europe.</span></li>
</ul>
<p><strong><a data-udi="umb://document/4c9fc09241f14e3c80acb89b5c9226dd" href="/{localLink:umb://document/4c9fc09241f14e3c80acb89b5c9226dd}" title="Selva">Find out more about Selva &gt;&gt;</a></strong></p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="g6">
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<h2>France</h2>
<p><img style="width: 100%; height: auto;" src="/media/13082533/2_photoingfrmrs1504aug15.jpg?width=0&amp;height=0" alt="" data-udi="umb://media/3fb6b11bf3814170af48016b0480a81e" /></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Walkers, hikers and trekkers alike will love the Morzine region of France. Mountain lovers can start their adventure on any one of the well maintained marked trails and routes. Take a walk through the forests, onto the high mountain tracks and up to the top of one of the towering peaks around Morzine. With over 200 kilometres of trails, you'll be spoilt for choice!</span></p>
<p><strong>What is there to see and do:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Nantaux</strong>: <span style="font-weight: 400;">The tallest mountain in Morzine and is accessible from Montriond. There are two routes, one that snakes round through the forests until you reach the ridge. The other route goes straight up and once a year there’s an annual race where super fit people run to the top.</span></p>
</li>
<li>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;"></span><span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>Le Lac de Myon Guerin</strong>: </span>This gentle walk will appeal to walkers of all abilities, with a gentle-graded walk that offers spectacular views without a great deal of effort. You can take in some spectacular 360° views from the top of Pointe de Nyon by taking the TeleSiege de la Pointe. This is near Nyon Guerin lake, a man made reservoir that supplies the snow cannons for Morzine’s ski area.</p>
</li>
<li><span style="font-weight: 400;"><strong>Le Roc d'Enfer</strong>: This summit is one of the highest peaks in the valley, providing extremely challenging hikes and treks. The exhilarating trails will reward you with wonderful views of the surrounding mountains and Lake Geneva.</span></li>
</ul>
<p><strong><a data-udi="umb://document/a95b5199e8e04283bf8eeeabb42715fc" href="/{localLink:umb://document/a95b5199e8e04283bf8eeeabb42715fc}" title="Morzine">Find out more about Morzine&gt;&gt;</a></strong></p>
</div>
</div>
<p> </p>
